    {
      "name": "PQC-5 - Detect Legacy TLS Cipher Suites",
      "description": "Detects legacy TLS cipher suites that are vulnerable to quantum attacks and should be replaced with PQC-ready alternatives",
      "rationale": "Legacy TLS cipher suites using RSA, ECDHE, or ECDSA will be vulnerable to quantum attacks. Applications should prepare for TLS 1.3 with post-quantum key exchange.",
      "remediation": "Configure TLS to use quantum-resistant cipher suites. Prepare for hybrid classical-quantum key exchange mechanisms.",
